NetPanzer Map Editor
====================

A Qt5-based map editor for the netPanzer open-source real-time strategy game.

Features
--------

- Open and save netPanzer .npm maps (binary format, verified round-trip)
- Tile painting with full undo/redo
- Ellipse paint tool — drag to paint tiles along an ellipse outline
- Rect select and stamp system — drag-select a region, save as a stamp, place with one click
- Tile pick tool — click any map tile to select it for painting
- Autotile — automatic transition-tile selection based on 8-neighbour bitmask;
  enabled when a .autotile.json sidecar is found alongside the tileset
  (see docs/autotile-format.md)
- Bundled generated tileset (no game data required); see docs/generated-tileset.md
- Tile browser with jump-to-ID search
- Place and move outpost and spawn-point objects
- Object renaming via double-click or context menu
- Minimap with viewport overlay and click-to-pan
- Zoom toward cursor
- Keyboard shortcuts: T (tile paint), E (ellipse), I (pick), R (rect select),
  M (stamp), O (place outpost), S (spawn point), V (select object), G (grid)

Building
--------

See BUILD.md for full build and AppImage instructions.

Quick start:

  $ meson setup build
  $ ninja -C build
  $ ./build/netpanzer-editor

